snippet: A South Korean official said the site, a 23-story apartment building under construction in Pyongyang, may have already housed dozens of families.
abstract: Apartment building under construction that housed more than 90 families collapses in Pyongyang, North Korea; government says there are 'human casualties' but does not give figures.
lead_paragraph: A South Korean official said the site, a 23-story apartment building under construction in Pyongyang, may have already housed dozens of families.

headline.main: North Korea Reports ‘Serious’ Collapse at Building Project Believed to House Dozens
headline.print_headline: North Korea Reports ‘Serious’ Collapse at Building Project Believed to House Dozens
